        oh and if the girls of mis-teeq are out there reading my posts...i in no way want anyone's feelings to be hurt ;). i wanted to give the uk fans an idea on what was going on with the hot 100 chart and u.s. music scene @ the time. nobody's a failure, ok? i've also seen huge u.s. acts like britney spears struggle to get into the hot 100 top 10 back then...and even after awhile usher himself couldn't notch anymore hot 100 top 10 hits.

        so i just wanted to clear that up! and same for any future uk acts i do u.s. hot 100 chart retrospects on...i don't think ANYONE is a failure! i just don't want mis-teeq to feel bad or have any regrets....there were also huge selling u.s. acts back then that couldn't compete with usher in the hot 100 top 10...so just wanted to tell the girls that :) i totally dig their music and couldn't be more happier and prouder of them for all their success in the uk and in europe. the u.s. is just too hard sometimes to make it for many international acts. esp. pre-social media and pre-internet.

        Sunshine Gal

        Vote score

        so 'scandalous' peaks @ #35 on the hot 100 chart for the wk of 7/10/2004....here's the link: https://www.billboard.c*m/charts/hot-100/2004-07-10

        now what was going on this wk here in the states is usher! as you can see he has the #2, 3 & 7 positions. his #7 song *yeah* was a huge #1 smash and you couldn't miss him on the radio. in 2004 billboard still hadn't made the comments section...it's too bad, cuz i could've passed along some ideas and suggestions for mis-teeq. see, just like today, when an artist is dominating the hot 100 top 10 with 2+ spots, it'll be awhile before they fall out of it ;)...but they won't be in there forever. as soon as usher falls out of the top 10, would've been a better time to release 'scandalous' in the u.s. or even a re-release ;)

        it's too bad mis-teeq never went on trl back then...i personally didn't know who they were or heard this single too much on u.s. radio. i also would've suggested they go on the disney channel and nickelodean and try to connect with the u.s. teen and pre-teen market. *and if they did, i would've had them go on repeatedly!* so to me, this was bad timing...cuz after usher's first single...he's never gonna leave the top 10 for about 1 year...his 2nd single *burn* will go in the top 10 as well as the 3rd single 'confessions' while 'yeah' is still in the top 10. even @ the end of this year, he'll have a big hit with alicia keys' 'my boo'....but again, all momentums cool down and the top 10 will continue to fluxuate. and all you had to do was follow the hot 100 chart for about a month to see usher dominate and stay put in the top 10.

        but congrats to mis-teeq for achieving great success in the uk. and scoring a top 40 hit over here is no easy feat.... usher! LOL! but i do love 'scandalous' and maybe, if their label tried one more time the following year after usher's momentum cooled down, maybe the results could've been different.

        hey what's up mates! so sorry i couldn't do my mis-teeq retrospect last time *had to upgrade my cable boxes*. ok, so mis-teeq had one hit over here in the states 'scandalous' (which i've been totally diggin'!!! and very addicted to it). let's take a look back on the hot 100 chart to find out why this wasn't a bigger hit over here ;) and thanks again to thierry hieron *sorry mate if i misspelled* for recommending that track to me ;)

        'scandalous' enters the hot 100 chart on 5/22/2004 @ #82-68-61-51-50-43-39-35-peak*-40-45-52-62 (and then falls off the chart not too long afterwards)

        ok, so like most songs, 'scandalous' enters @ the bottom of the chart and works it's way up (very normal back then, i've seen destiny's child back in the day go thru the same thing)...and it takes about 7 wks to crack the top 40. so what that tells me, the top 10-20 just isn't budging! and/or 'scandalous' just can't make a bigger impact on u.s. radio. it stays in the top 40 for about 3 wks but starts falling down the chart. i'll put up the hot 100 chart *hopefully!* for the peak week in my next post.
